node.text:
I am so grateful for all the things I am doing and experiencing!  I don’t have the words to express how thankful I am for everything I am working on right now.  Life is beautiful and it becomes even more beautiful when you fully experience and live life in the moment. ⁣
I can’t wait to share all the things I have been working on and how each and everyday I am learning and growing.   I hope every time you see my fitness posts, videos, bikini shoots and read my blogs I inspire you to love yourself more and to live your life to its fullest potential.  ⁣
I had the great pleasure to visit and work in beautiful Puerto Rico with some amazing people @jj_photo_art, @joelenriquefilms and @jiomphoto shot at the breath taking @ritzcarltondoradobeach.  It is a tropical paradise and it still feels like a dream.⁣ 🌴
⁣
www.erianton.com⁣
⁣
Video: @joelenriquefilms⁣
Wearing: 👙 @kl_swimwear and @sanlorenzo_bikinis⁣
⁣
⁣
#PuertoRico⁣
#DoradoBeach

node.text:
My killer core and leg ankle weight (10 lbs) beach workout powered by @Redline_Energy  Noo-Fusion Cotton Candy. 🦋⁣
⁣⁣
1️⃣ Alternating single leg lifts⁣⁣
4 sets - 25 reps each leg⁣⁣
2️⃣ Bicycle kicks ⁣⁣
4 sets - 25 reps each leg⁣⁣
3️⃣ Leg lifts (pro-style)⁣⁣
4 sets - 25 reps ⁣⁣
4️⃣ Leg Lifts ⁣⁣
4 sets - 25 reps each leg⁣⁣
5️⃣ Kick backs⁣⁣
4 sets - 25 reps each leg⁣⁣
6️⃣ Stepping leg curls⁣⁣
4 sets - 25 reps each leg⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Noo-Fusion is a carbonated pre-workout that improves cognitive and mental function.  When I am training on the beach in the hot sun drinking Noo-Fusion with 300 mg of caffeine, Cognizin (250 mg), Teacrine, Yohimbe, Super Creatine and Betaine (2.5 g) help to support my focus, energy, performance, reaction time and have the best workouts!.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Follow the inventor of redline: @BangEnergy.CEO 😎⁣⁣

node.text:
Making my healthy snack fudge protein balls with @BangEnergy Cherry Blade Lemonade 💜⁣
⁣
On low heat mix and melt:⁣
Coconut oil - 2 tbsp⁣
Peanut Butter - 1 large spoonful ⁣
Honey - 2 tbsp. ⁣
⁣
Then add in and mix well:⁣
Oats - 1 cup⁣
Chocolate protein powder - 1 scoop. ⁣
⁣
Remove from heat and let cool, form balls and put in refrigerator until hard.  Makes 6-8 protein balls⁣
⁣
